⭐ CUSTOMER APP — EXACTLY WHAT IT MUST SHOW + DO

Think “Swiggy consumer app”.
Fast, clean, idiot-proof.

1. Auth & Profile

Shows:

Phone number input

OTP screen

Profile info (name, phone, email)

Address list

Does:

Login with OTP

Add/Edit/Delete addresses

2. Home & Catalog

Shows:

Categories

Item cards (image, name, price, rating)

Search bar

Filters (brand, price, type)

Does:

Browse categories

Search items

Filter results

View product details

3. Product Details

Shows:

Images

Price & description

Item specifications

Add to cart button

Reviews

Does:

Add to cart

Change quantity

4. Cart

Shows:

List of items

Quantity selector

Total price

Delivery address

Delivery charges

Does:

Edit quantity

Remove items

Proceed to checkout

5. Checkout

Shows:

Order summary

Delivery address

Payment options

Coupon option

Does:

Complete payment

Create order

Redirect to success screen

6. Order Tracking

Shows:

Order ID

Vendor assigned (name, phone)

Status timeline (placed → accepted → picked → delivered)

Delivery ETA

Map (optional)

Does:

Cancel order

Contact vendor via chat

7. Chat

Shows:

Chat with vendor

Message history

Does:

Send/receive messages realtime

8. Order History

Shows:

Past orders

Total spent

Order details

Does:

Reorder

View invoice

9. Notifications

Shows:

Order updates

Vendor messages

✔ That’s the customer app.
Nothing more. Nothing less.

⭐ VENDOR APP — EXACTLY WHAT IT MUST SHOW + DO

Think “Swiggy Partner App” but simplified.

1. Auth / Registration

Shows:

Business registration form

Upload documents

Store details

Location picker

Does:

Submit vendor application

Login via OTP

Wait-for-approval screen

2. Home Dashboard

Shows:

Today's orders count

Pending orders

Earnings summary

Availability toggle (online/offline)

3. Incoming Orders (Realtime)

Shows:

New order popup

Items list

Delivery address

Order value

ETA/distance

Does:

Accept

Reject
(Redis lock ensures first accept wins)

4. Active Order Workflow

Shows:

Order details

Customer address

Route info

Items

Does:

Mark:

Accepted

Packed

Out for delivery

Delivered

Update notes if needed

5. Chat

Shows:

Chat with customer

Message history

Does:

Send/receive messages realtime

6. Past Orders

Shows:

Completed orders

Earnings per order

Dates

7. Vendor Profile

Shows:

Store info

Rating

Timing

Does:

Edit store details

Edit availability

8. Notifications

Shows:

New orders

Customer messages

Admin updates

✔ That’s the vendor app.
It should be ruthlessly simple because vendors don’t have time for nonsense.

⭐ ADMIN PANEL — EXACTLY WHAT IT MUST SHOW + DO

This is your Swiggy Admin Dashboard.

1. Dashboard

Shows:

Total orders

Total revenue

Active vendors

Top categories

Daily/weekly stats

2. Inventory Management

Shows:

Item list with filters

Add/edit item form

Upload images

Category management

Does:

Add item

Edit item

Delete item

Bulk upload

3. Vendor Management

Shows:

Vendor list

Registration requests

Business details

Documents uploaded

Does:

Approve vendor

Reject vendor

Block/unblock vendor

Edit vendor details

4. Customer Management

Shows:

Customer list

Customer details

Order history

Does:

Block/unblock customer

5. Order Management

Shows:

All orders

Status filters

Customer & vendor details

Does:

Reassign vendor

Refund

Cancel order

Change order status (override)

6. System Config

Shows:

Radius settings

Order timeout value

Commission %

Tax settings

Does:

Update system rules

7. Payments & Reports

Shows:

Vendor payouts

Refunds

Transaction logs

Does:

Export CSV

Run reports

✔ Admin panel is your brain center.

⭐ FINAL SUMMARY (YOU CAN BUILD FROM THIS WITHOUT CONFUSION)
Customer App =

order → pay → track → chat → history

Vendor App =

receive → accept → deliver → chat → earnings

Admin Web =

inventory → vendors → orders → reports → system configs